column2: Migrated from EPA STORET Legacy Database- originally reported by Wisconsin DNR
Sunny- slight. chop- lake turning over- green in protected areas
Sunny- 4-6" chop- surface dirt- needles- leaves- etc.  Lake level: very high
Sunny- 4-6" waves- water discolored (tamarack).  Lake level: very high

Partly cloudy. Lakefront homeowners asked what they thought of the condition of the lake compared to past years-"water seemed clearer and less silty-less brown 'fuzz' on the kids when they get out"- "really cold about 8" off the surface"- "awesome". Kayaked out to deepest part of the lake-dragonflies- muskrat kept me company.
Not as much 'matter' in the water.
partly sunny-8mph wind-1 boat passing through-no wildlife spotted
sunny with light wind----1 boat passing through-----a gaggle of geese ( 5 ) spotted----pine tree pollen visible in the water column
partly sunny light wind ----- no boats ---- no wildlife spotted
sunny with light wind------1 boat passing through----no wild life spotted
sunny with a light wind----particles suspended in the water column---no boats--no wildlife
sunny calm wind----no wildlife spotted---1 boat passing through----no wildlife spotted---green on lake surface
sunny with a light wind---no wildlife spotted---no boats---looking through the water column is like looking through a muddy snow globe
